The paper studies user behavior in non-atomic congestion games, which are a type of game theory problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory). The paper also uses techniques from optimization and analysis, which could place it in categories such as cs.NE (Network Economics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the scalability and gaugeability of non-atomic congestion games, which could place it in the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
